x4freetext: The U-238 Targets were Prepared by Electrodeposition
.The Total Chain Yields were Determined For
Mass Chains in Which the Yields of the Product Nuclides
/by Authors/.Experiments were Carried Out at Two
Incident Energies, 9.4 and 12.4 MeV, at the Target
Position,Which Correspond to the Compound Excitation
Beam at R2 Course of the JAERI Tandem Van De Graff
For the Measurement of Products of the Half-Lives
Shorter Than 30 Min Down to Seconds Authors Used
a Gas-Jet Transport System,While the Product
Nuclides with Half-Lives Longer Than 10 Min were
Measured by the Conventional Radiochemical Technique
Combining Stacked-Target Irradiation and Ge Gamma-Ray
Spectrometry with or Without Chemical Separation.
